com.joliciel.talismane.parser

Interface ParseConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ClassificationSolution, Comparable<ParseConfiguration>, HasFeatureCache, ParseConfigurationWrapper, RankingSolution, Solution

    public interface ParseConfiguration
extends Comparable<ParseConfiguration>, ClassificationSolution, RankingSolution, ParseConfigurationWrapper, HasFeatureCache
    A sequence of dependency arcs applied to a given sequence of pos-tagged tokens, as well as the stack and buffer indicating the pos-tagged tokens already visited and not yet visited.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli

      • addManualNonProjectiveDependency

        DependencyArc addManualNonProjectiveDependency(PosTaggedToken head,
                                             PosTaggedToken dependent,
                                             String label)
        Add the given dependency to the current configuration's non-projective dependency set. This should only be used when reading a previously annotated corpus, to indicate the projective and non-projective governor for a given token. If the transition system is capable of producing its own non-projective dependencies there should be no need to distinguish between projective and non-projective.
        Parameters:
        head -
        dependent -
        label -
        Returns:
